description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:
   package subpackage;

   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println("Hello");
       }
   }

2. Compile using the following command:
   ajc -d subpackage subpackage\Test.java

Observation: A directory "subpackage" is created under the existing "subpackage" directory.

Expected Behavior: It would be nice to have the same behavior as javac.

Steps to Reproduce: Use the -d option while correctly compiling classes from the subpackage.
